[
    {
        "content": "<p>I have written a <a href=\"https://y86-dev.github.io/blog/safe-pinned-initialization/overview.html\">blog post</a> presenting an overview over safe pinned initialization. It also presents some solutions to the problem. While I posted it on the rust internals forum, I figured that some of you might not be following it closely, so I posted it here as well.</p>",
        "id": 300525742,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664019950
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for working on this! Pinned initialization seems to be one of the most consistently recurring challenges.</p>",
        "id": 300527884,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664020976
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you think this solution is usable for initially Rust-level self-referential structs -- ala <a href=\"https://crates.io/crates/ouroboros\">https://crates.io/crates/ouroboros</a></p>",
        "id": 300529460,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664021764
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am not sure what you mean by \"initially\". I have implemented <a href=\"https://github.com/y86-dev/simple-safe-init/blob/experiment/examples/linked_list.rs\"><code>list_head</code></a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/y86-dev/simple-safe-init/blob/experiment/examples/mutex.rs\"><code>mutex</code></a> from the kernel in Rust.</p>",
        "id": 300529853,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664021983
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Err, _initializing_. Interesting typo I did there.</p>",
        "id": 300529998,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664022033
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah this solution would be suitable for that. In the macro you can specify an identifier which will be of type <code>NonNull&lt;Self&gt;</code>. From the <code>list_head</code> example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PinInitializer</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">next</span>: <span class=\"nc\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Link</span>::<span class=\"n\">new_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">},</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">prev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Link</span>::<span class=\"n\">new_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">},</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pin</span>: <span class=\"nc\">PhantomPinned</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 300530253,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664022163
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just to make sure, you are aware that <code>ouroboros</code> allocates memory for each self referential field.</p>",
        "id": 300530481,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664022283
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah -- my current uses of ouroboros are all in user-space where that sort of thing is more ok :-) My understanding is that <code>Box</code> shouldn't be required, but they couldn't figure out how to get something right without it.</p>",
        "id": 300530643,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664022354
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/certificate.rs#L56-L63\">https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/certificate.rs#L56-L63</a> is a typical use case</p>",
        "id": 300530859,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664022469
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/safe.20pinned.20initialization/near/300530643\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yeah -- my current uses of ouroboros are all in user-space where that sort of thing is more ok :-) My understanding is that <code>Box</code> shouldn't be required, but they couldn't figure out how to get something right without it.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>There are multiple problems associated with not introducing an indirection through <code>Box</code>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>pointers to types with self references cannot be marked <code>noalias</code> (otherwise we would get incorrect optimizations).</li>\n<li>self referential types must have a stable address, or need to correct the references to them upon getting moved.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There are fixes, but they result in worse ergonomics.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>pointers pointing to types that are <code>!Unpin</code> do not receive the <code>noalias</code> tag.</li>\n<li>because rust has no move operator overload, we cannot really correct a moved self referential structure and are forced to use <code>Pin</code>. As you probably know, <code>Pin</code> has rather poor ergonomics.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In userspace it is generally ok to add additional indirection/allocation and ouroboros chooses it, because then the self referential types can still be moved. So users do not need to rewrite their APIs.</p>",
        "id": 300531666,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664022834
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>FWIW, I was expirementing with an imperative API for in-place initialization: <a href=\"https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2021&amp;gist=cf2f1460531e6a983033173dbd87e16c\">https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2021&amp;gist=cf2f1460531e6a983033173dbd87e16c</a></p>\n<p>It's super verbose, so I'd want to implement a macro to generate it all, but hopefully you can see the idea.</p>",
        "id": 300532058,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664023047
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You might want to check out <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span>'s <a href=\"https://crates.io/crates/pin-init\"><code>pin-init</code></a> crate.<del> It essentially does exactly this, but with macros.</del> It does this via a closure and other macros.</p>",
        "id": 300532268,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664023133
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>wait sorry that is incorrect</p>",
        "id": 300532359,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664023179
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The closure is just to make sure it's pin initialized</p>",
        "id": 300532537,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1664023260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For unpinned field it actually generates builder functions that take values.</p>",
        "id": 300532592,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1664023289
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, then I didnt mix them up <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span> (FYI I also tried to add this in my own crate, but ended up creating something with unsoundness).</p>",
        "id": 300532738,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664023349
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(It'll be unsound to pin-initialize a unpinned field)</p>",
        "id": 300532857,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1664023400
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/safe.20pinned.20initialization/near/300530859\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/certificate.rs#L56-L63\">https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/certificate.rs#L56-L63</a> is a typical use case</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I have only briefly looked at the code, so what I say might not be completely accurate. I do not think that my library can help you yet. It is designed to work with direct self references, in e.g.:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">MyBuf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">buf</span>: <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">64</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// ptr points into buf</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In your code, you want to borrow from an <code>Arc</code> that is also contained inside the same struct. This is slightly different from what my library is designed to do (as <code>Arc</code> already permits multiple references into the same data).</p>\n<p>I do not really understand the architecture of your code, why is it necessary to own the certificate? Is it to avoid copying the data and avoid sprinkling lifetimes all over the place?</p>",
        "id": 300538801,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664026421
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think my library can be extended to support help with a DAG</p>",
        "id": 300539110,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1664026569
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, the goal is to have a single allocation of the buffer, and then another struct with a bunch of pointers into it. And then you can pass the value containing both of them around together.</p>",
        "id": 300539163,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664026607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hmm I think that you would not need the <code>ouroboros::AliasableBox</code> wrapper for the <code>Arc</code>, because the <code>Arc</code> <em>already</em> allows multiple references.</p>",
        "id": 300539361,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664026709
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the only challenge you would have would be to have some kind of <code>'this</code> lifetime.</p>",
        "id": 300539386,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664026732
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, perhaps this is really orthagonal to what we need for the kernel. But I'd be so happy if we solved both at once :-)</p>",
        "id": 300539602,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664026850
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So essentially it would look like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">// inner type generated by some proc macro</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// this is only used by Cert</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">CertInner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">raw</span>: <span class=\"nc\">RawCert</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// this lifetime is not actually static,, as it is only valid for the lifetime of Cert</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CertInner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parse</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">RawCert</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// here we create raw with parse and a cheated 'static lifetime from data</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">raw</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Cert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span>: <span class=\"nc\">CertInner</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Cert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parse</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">RawCert</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span>: <span class=\"nc\">CertInner</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parse</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So all in all <em>very</em> similar to ouroboros, but without the extra allocation.</p>",
        "id": 300540233,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664027141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe this could be added to ouroboros via some kind of attribute?</p>",
        "id": 300540270,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664027153
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411490\">@Alex Gaynor</span> do you have some problem resulting from having to use ouroboros?</p>",
        "id": 300540376,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664027184
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We ship it to production now, so it does work. The biggest areas for improvement IMO:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Not needing AliasableBox when the value is already on the heap (e.g. <code>Arc&lt;T&gt;</code>)</li>\n<li>Having an official way to do this would increase confidence it's all correct</li>\n<li>Better support for mapping values: <a href=\"https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/crl.rs#L436\">https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/crl.rs#L436</a> (I don't think pinned initialization would change this though)</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 300544939,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Gaynor",
        "timestamp": 1664029535
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/safe.20pinned.20initialization/near/300544939\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Not needing AliasableBox when the value is already on the heap (e.g. <code>Arc&lt;T&gt;</code>)</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think you could try to file an issue with ouroboros in the short term. To me it seems like that would be something they could support.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/safe.20pinned.20initialization/near/300544939\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Having an official way to do this would increase confidence it's all correct</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n<p>For sure! I have not thought about this in detail, but as I see it right now, the task of adding this to the language itself is going to be very difficult.<br>\nNot that it cannot be done, but expressing the \"this field borrows from that field\" thing <em>and</em> guaranteeing safety is going to be <em>very</em> complicated... So I think for the moment you will have to make do with ouroboros.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411490\">Alex Gaynor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/safe.20pinned.20initialization/near/300544939\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Better support for mapping values: <a href=\"https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/crl.rs#L436\">https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/blob/main/src/rust/src/x509/crl.rs#L436</a> (I don't think pinned initialization would change this though)</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why do you have to keep the original data around? Is there a problem with just borrowing the data and using lifetimes? Or do you have to keep that for python compatibility?</p>",
        "id": 300560437,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664037801
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">y86</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/safe.20pinned.20initialization/near/300525742\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I have written a <a href=\"https://y86-dev.github.io/blog/safe-pinned-initialization/overview.html\">blog post</a> presenting an overview over safe pinned initialization. It also presents some solutions to the problem. While I posted it on the rust internals forum, I figured that some of you might not be following it closely, so I posted it here as well.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you have any comments on the post?</p>",
        "id": 300560479,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1664037827
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span> do you know any situation where we would need the address of the initialized type to decide whether the initialization fails? If not, we could just move the evaluation of the fields out of the closure (this could lead to better optimizations, though I am not sure):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#![feature(allocator_api, new_uninit)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">__init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">place</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">InitClosure</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span>: <span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InitClosure</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">__init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">place</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)(</span><span class=\"n\">place</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InitClosure</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">from_closure</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span>: <span class=\"nc\">F</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">F</span>: <span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"fm\">macro_rules!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span>:<span class=\"nc\">ident</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">$($field</span>:<span class=\"nc\">ident</span>: <span class=\"cp\">$val</span>:<span class=\"nc\">expr</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">$(,</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$field</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$val</span><span class=\"p\">;)</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">place</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span>::<span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">ptr</span>::<span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>::<span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">ptr</span>::<span class=\"n\">addr_of_mut</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">place</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"cp\">$field</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$field</span><span class=\"p\">);)</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">#[allow(unreachable_code)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kc\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>: <span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"cp\">$($field</span>: ::<span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"fm\">todo!</span><span class=\"p\">()),</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$crate</span>::<span class=\"n\">InitClosure</span>::<span class=\"n\">from_closure</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InitPtr</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>